# Delphi Library Development Rules (Advanced)

You are assisting with a large Delphi (Object Pascal) codebase.

CRITICAL LIMITATIONS:
- No LSP
- No full project awareness
- Work only with provided context

GENERAL RULES:
- Keep units compilable
- Do not break public API
- Minimize changes
- Avoid new dependencies

USES:
- Maintain correct uses sections
- Respect interface/implementation separation
- Avoid circular dependencies

ERROR FIXING:
- Use compiler output as source of truth
- Fix missing units
- Fix type mismatches
- Fix signatures

REFACTORING:
- Only refactor provided code
- Do not assume global changes
- Keep backward compatibility 

TLS / LOW-LEVEL:
- Follow RFC strictly
- Do not invent behavior
- Prefer minimal changes
- Highlight uncertainty

WORKFLOW:
1. Code change
2. Build
3. Paste errors
4. Fix incrementally

PRIORITY:
Correctness > Safety > Minimal change > Readability